"Evans W.F.J., Puckrin E.","A wintertime measurement of the greenhouse radiation from nitrous oxide",1997,"Canadian Journal of Analytical Sciences and Spectroscopy","42","5",,"141","145",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0031320226&partnerID=40&md5=d4763f8492703b35c3854bd892e8ace1","Trent University, Environmental Resource Studies, Peterborough, Ont. K9J 7B8, Canada","Evans, W.F.J., Trent University, Environmental Resource Studies, Peterborough, Ont. K9J 7B8, Canada; Puckrin, E., Trent University, Environmental Resource Studies, Peterborough, Ont. K9J 7B8, Canada","Ground-based, thermal emission measurements of the cold, clear sky have been made and showed several emission bands in the mid-infrared region that are associated with nitrous oxide (N2O). A spectrum of the background atmospheric emission in the absence of any N2O has been simulated using the FASCD3P line-by-line radiation code with measured radiosonde parameters of pressure, temperature and relative humidity. The simulated spectrum has been used to extract the thermal emission bands of N2O from the total atmospheric emission spectrum. It was determined that incorporating an N2O mixing ratio of 316±35 ppbv in the simulations provided excellent agreement with the measured radiance. The downward greenhouse flux at the surface associated with the 1100-1350 cm-1 bands of N2O was measured to be 0.80 W/m2 ± 12% for cold winter conditions. The flux for all the infrared bands of N2O has been estimated to be 1.43 W/m2 ± 12%.","FTIR spectroscopy; Global warming; Greenhouse gas; Nitrous oxide; Radiative flux",,,,,,,"Houghton, J.T., Meira L.G. Filho, Callander, B.A., Harris, N., Kattenberg, A., Maskell, K., (1996) Climate Change 1995, The Science of Climate Change, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Khalil, M.A.K., Rasmussen, R.A., (1992) J. Geophys. Res., 97, p. 14651; Mahlman, J., Levy, H., Moxim, W., (1986) J. Geophys. Res., 91, p. 2687; Prinn, R., Cunnold, D., Rasmussen, R., Simmonds, P., Alyea, F., Crawford, A., Fraser, P., Rosen, R., (1990) J. Geophys. Res., 95, p. 18369; Crutzen, Q.J.R., (1970) Meteorol. Soc., 96, p. 320; McElroy, M., McConnell, J., (1971) J. Atmos. Sci., 28, p. 1095; Wayne, R.P., (1991) Chemistry of Atmospheres, 2nd Edition, , 447 pp., Clarendon Press, Oxford; Clough, S.A., Kneizys, F.X., Anderson, G.P., Shettle, E.P., Chetwynd, J.H., Abreu, L.W., Hall, L.A., (1988) IRS '88: Current Problems in Atmospheric Radiation, p. 372. , J. Lenoble and J.F. Geleyn (eds.); Evans, W.F.J., Puckrin, E., (1994) Geophys. Res. Lett., 21, p. 2381; Evans, W.F.J., Puckrin, E., (1994) Can. J. Appl. Spectrosc., 39, p. 85; Evans, W.F.J., Puckrin, E., (1995) J. Clim., 8, p. 3091; Evans, W.F.J., Puckrin, E., (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, p. 1769; Ellingson, R.G., Ellis, J., Fels, S., (1991) J. Geophys. Res., 96, p. 8929; Wang, W.C., Yung, Y.L., Lacis, A.A., Mo, T., Hanser, J.E., (1976) Science, 194, p. 685; Donner, L., Ramanathan, V., (1980) J. Atmos. Sci., 37, p. 119; Ramanathan, V., Cicerone, R.J., Singh, H.B., Kiehl, J.T., (1985) J. Geophys. Res., 90, p. 5547; Feigelson, E.M., Fomin, B.A., Gorchakova, I.A., Rozanov, E.V., Timofeyev, Y.M., Trotsenko, A.N., Schwarzkopf, M.D., (1991) J. Geophys. Res., 96, p. 8985; Clough, S.A., Iacono, M.J., (1995) J. Geophys. Res., 100, p. 16519; Hauglustaine, D.A., Granier, C., Brasseur, G.P., Mégie, G., (1994) J. Geophys. Res., 99, p. 1173; Anderson, G.P., Clough, S.A., Kneizys, F.X., Chetwynd, J.H., Shettle, E.P., (1986) AFGL Atmospheric Constituent Profiles (0-120 km), AFGL-TR-86-0110, , Optical Physics Div., Air Force Geophysics Laboratory, Hanscom AFB, MA; Rothman, L.S., Gamache, R.R., Tipping, R.H., Rinsland, C.P., Smith, M.A.H., Benner, D.C., Devi, V.M., Toth, R.A., (1992) J. Quant. Spectrosc. Radiat. Transfer, 48, p. 469","Evans, W.F.J.; Trent University, Environmental Resource Studies, Peterborough, Ont. K9J 7B8, Canada",,,,,,,,12056685,,,,"English","Can. J. Anal. Sci. Spectrosc.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-003